08/08/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- EUFOR teams in Macedonia discovered planted mines on the local road leading towards the border villages of Tanuse, Grekaj, Ribnica and Bibaj near the border with Albania, <I>Dnevnik</I> daily reported on Thursday (7 August).According to Dnevnik's sources, EUFOR informed the defence ministry, but the ministry has rejected the information. 
The mines were probably planted in the area during the 2001 military conflict in the country. 
(Dnevnik - 07/08/03)
